Explanation:

The problem requires finding the smallest positive integer n that is divisible by k and consists only of the digit 1. We can solve this by iteratively multiplying 10 (representing the digit 1) until we reach or exceed k. Since the problem only considers the length of the result, we can return the result after the iteration. This solution has a constant time complexity (O(1)) and constant space complexity (O(1)), making it efficient for solving the problem.

